yntax is not a universal property of all living languages, the issue of how to detect and define syntactic complexity has been revived with a combination of classical and new arguments. This volume contains contributions about the formal complexity of natural language, about specific issues of clausal embedding, and about syntactic complexity in terms of grammar-external interfaces in the domain of language acquisition.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aFormalization (Linguistics) 0aGenerative grammar. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxClauses. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxSyntax. 0aLanguage arts. 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aClausal Embedding.  aGrammar Theory.  aInterface Syntax.  aSyntactic Complexity.1 aBauke, Leah S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBayer, Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBayer, Josef, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBecker, Misha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrey, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKluck, Marlies, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoeper, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSauerland, Uli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrotzke, Andreas , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTrotzke, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTruckenbrodt, Hubert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVeenstra, Tonjes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZwart, Jan-Wouter, econtributor.